alk with his head lowered. They miscalculated their impetus and were carried past. When they succeeded in approaching him the man smacked his lips and slowly turned toward them. Yes, it was Karl, but what a Karl — his face blank, his eyes glazed! 'I'm just taking a rest,' he said in a dull voice. 'I'll continue in a minute.' Suddenly a taxi with its flag up came rolling slowly over the deserted asphalt. 'Stop him,' said Karl. 'I want him to take me.' The car drew up. Günther kept tumbling ove